  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Sequential administration of MSCs obtained from adipose tissue is an effective and safe
      treatment for acute graft versus host disease refractory to first-line treatment. Furthermore
      the infusion of these cells produces a biological pattern in patients that relates to the
      clinical response.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Multicenter, open, non -controlled clinical trial. It is a phase I-II trial to assess the
      safety and efficacy of sequential infusion of allogeneic MSCs from adipose tissue, expanded
      &quot;in vitro&quot; platelet lysate in the treatment of patients undergoing hematopoietic stem cell
      trasplantation, who have developed a refractory graft versus host disease to first line of
      treatment.

      This is a prospective, multicenter, open to patients undergoing allogeneic transplantation in
      Spanish hospitals, with one cohort of patients who receive four sequential doses of MSC.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
